Definition: plays stressing the irrational or illogical aspects of life, usually to show that modern life is pointless
Example: Samuel Beckett and Eugene Ionesco have written plays for the theater of the absurd
Synonyms: play, plays, stressing, the, irrational, or, illogical, aspects, of, life, usually, to, show, that, modern, is, pointless, Samuel, Beckett, and, Eugene, Ionesco, have, written, for, theater, absurd
Category: noun.communication
